<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1627,1978]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis box="[189,543,1700,1726]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
Notes:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. M. Liang &amp; S. T. Liu" authorityYear="2021" box="[288,543,1700,1726]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniastraceae" genus="Hyalopsora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="minispora">Hyalopsora minispora</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[700,910,1700,1725]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniastraceae" genus="Hyalopsora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="cryptogrammes">
<emphasis box="[700,910,1700,1725]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">H. cryptogrammes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[970,1135,1699,1725]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniastraceae" genus="Hyalopsora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="hakodatens">
<emphasis box="[970,1135,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">H. hakodatens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in spore size. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. M. Liang &amp; S. T. Liu" authorityYear="2021" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniastraceae" genus="Hyalopsora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="minispora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">H. minispora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has both urediniospores and amphispores while 
<taxonomicName box="[823,1035,1736,1761]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniastraceae" genus="Hyalopsora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="cryptogrammes">
<emphasis box="[823,1035,1736,1761]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">H. cryptogrammes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only urediniospores (
<bibRefCitation author="Sydow, P. &amp; Sydow, H." pageId="3" pageNumber="44" pagination="651 - 654" refId="ref5299" refString="Sydow, P. &amp; Sydow, H. (1914) Monographia uredinearum seu specierum omnium ad hunc usque diem cognitarum descriptio et adumbratio systematica. Science 39: 651 - 654. https: // doi. org / 10.1126 / science. 39.1009.651" type="journal article" year="1914">Sydow &amp; Sydow 1914</bibRefCitation>
). Urediniospores of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. M. Liang &amp; S. T. Liu" authorityYear="2021" box="[506,654,1772,1797]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniastraceae" genus="Hyalopsora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="minispora">
<emphasis box="[506,654,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">H. minispora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have 4–6 scattered germ pores, but 
<taxonomicName box="[1053,1233,1771,1797]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniastraceae" genus="Hyalopsora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="hakodatensis">
<emphasis box="[1053,1233,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">H. hakodatensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses only 2–4 germ pores at the equatorial region (
<bibRefCitation author="Ji, J. X. &amp; Li, Z. &amp; Li, Y. &amp; Zhuang, J. Y. &amp; Kakishima, M." box="[543,694,1807,1834]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" pagination="23 - 29" refId="ref4683" refString="Ji, J. X., Li, Z., Li, Y., Zhuang, J. Y. &amp; Kakishima, M. (2018) Notes on rust fungi in China 4. Hosts and distribution of Hyalopsora aspidiotus and H. hakodatensis. Mycotaxon 133 (1): 23 - 29. https: // doi. org / 10.5248 / 133.23" type="journal article" year="2018">
Ji 
<emphasis box="[570,626,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. M. Liang &amp; S. T. Liu" authorityYear="2021" box="[712,861,1808,1833]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniastraceae" genus="Hyalopsora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="minispora">
<emphasis box="[712,861,1808,1833]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">H. minispora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares the host 
<taxonomicName box="[1039,1174,1807,1833]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Blechnaceae" genus="Blechnopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1039,1174,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Blechnopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kamei" authorityYear="1932" box="[1239,1369,1807,1833]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniastraceae" genus="Hyalopsora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="aculeata">
<emphasis box="[1239,1369,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">H. aculeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ono 2017)" baseAuthorityName="Ono" baseAuthorityYear="2017" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniastraceae" genus="Hyalopsora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="polypodii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">H. polypodii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ono, Y." box="[258,377,1844,1870]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" pagination="37 - 56" refId="ref5076" refString="Ono, Y. (2017) Rust fungi (Pucciniales) in northern Ibaraki Prefecture, Japan. Journal of General Plant Pathology 66: 37 - 56." type="journal article" year="2017">Ono 2017</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. M. Liang &amp; S. T. Liu" authorityYear="2021" box="[514,664,1844,1869]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniastraceae" genus="Hyalopsora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="minispora">
<emphasis box="[514,664,1844,1869]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">H. minispora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has urediniospores and amphispores in the same uredinium, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kamei" authorityYear="1932" box="[136,267,1879,1906]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniastraceae" genus="Hyalopsora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="aculeata">
<emphasis box="[136,156,1880,1905]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[171,267,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">aculeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only urediniospores (
<bibRefCitation author="Hiratsuka, N. &amp; Sato, S. &amp; Katsuya, K. &amp; Kakishima, M. &amp; Hiratsuka, Y. &amp; Kaneko, S. &amp; Ono, Y. &amp; Sato, T. &amp; Harada, Y. &amp; Hiratsuka, T. &amp; Nakayama, K." box="[557,800,1879,1906]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" refId="ref4615" refString="Hiratsuka, N., Sato, S., Katsuya, K., Kakishima, M., Hiratsuka, Y., Kaneko, S., Ono, Y., Sato, T., Harada, Y., Hiratsuka, T. &amp; Nakayama, K. (1992) The rust flora of Japan. Tsukuba: Tsukuba Shuppankai." type="book" year="1992">
Hiratsuka 
<emphasis box="[676,725,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">et al</emphasis>
. 1992
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. M. Liang &amp; S. T. Liu" authorityYear="2021" box="[820,968,1880,1905]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniastraceae" genus="Hyalopsora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="minispora">
<emphasis box="[820,968,1880,1905]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">H. minispora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ono" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[1275,1416,1879,1905]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniastraceae" genus="Hyalopsora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="polypodii">
<emphasis box="[1275,1416,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">H. polypodii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its smaller urediniospores (16.5–23.0 × 11.0–19.0 μm) with 4–6 scattered germ pores, those of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ono" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[1199,1339,1915,1941]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniastraceae" genus="Hyalopsora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="polypodii">
<emphasis box="[1199,1339,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">H. polypodii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are larger (18.0–37.5 × 8.0–22.5 μm) with 2–4 scattered germ pores (
<bibRefCitation author="Azbukina, Z. M." box="[797,976,1951,1978]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" refId="ref4073" refString="Azbukina, Z. M. (2015) Definitorium fungorum Rossiae, Ordo Pucciniales 1. Dalnauka, Vladivostok. [In Russina]" type="book" year="2015">Azbukina 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
